The paper deals with algorithms for deleting a point from a triangulation, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves data structures and algorithms for efficient computation, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of Delaunay triangulation and geometric information systems suggests cs.GR (Graphics) as another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the complexity of the algorithm, which involves numerical computations, indicating cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and data structures to solve a specific problem, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
